author: Amy Harder
title: Yes, oil prices are negative. No, you won’t get paid to fill up your tank.
description: In an unprecedented move, U.S. oil prices went negative Monday — meaning, companies paid to sell their oil — but don’t expect to get paid to fill up your tank at the gas station. How it works: Several other layers of costs, including refinement, transportatio…
